condition.narrative: Ethiopia, Kenya and Tanzania:Section I.A.3(c) of Schedule 2 to each country Financing Agreement1. The Recipient shall, not laterthan forty-five (45) days after the Effective Date, ensure that the respective RFTIs have, in form and substance satisfactory tothe Association: (i) established respective project implementation units with appropriate terms of reference and mandate; and (ii)adequate staff with qualifications, terms of reference and experience, acceptable to the Association.

Ethiopia, Kenya and Tanzania:Section I.B.1 of Schedule 2 to Financing Agreement1. The Recipient shall, not later than May 15 forEthiopia and August 31 for Kenya and Tanzania, in each calendar year during Project implementation, prepare, in cooperation withthe pertinent RFTIs and furnish to the Association, a program of activities proposed for inclusion in the Project during thefollowing fiscal year (Annual Work Plan), including: (a) a detailed timetable and budget for the sequencing and implementation ofsaid activities; and (b) the types of expenditures required for such activities.
